<TITLE> Stocks open down </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com)Stocks opened downbeat Tuesday with banks, mutual funds, power, pharmaceuticals and state run oil company Jamuna pacing the trade. The market saw prices of bank shares slumping due to profit taking amid power shares selling higher. Dhaka Stock Exchange kicked off with a slight decline in the general index which afterwards remained more or less stable till the midday sessions The benchmark DGEN or general index at 12.34 pm was down 11 points or 0.37 percent to 2937.71 while the DSI or all share price index was at 2472.99, down 10.52 or 0.42 percent. Turnover amounted to Tk 914.249 million from trading of 3,635,144 shares. Gainers outnumbered losers 125 to 67 with some 12 issues holding steady. At 12.37 pm, UCBL appeared at the peak of the turnover board, selling down at Tk 3745 from Monday's Tk 4015.25. AB Bank which gained on Monday also fell to Tk 2799 from Tk 2805. State-run power entity DESCO advanced to Tk 1098 from Tk 1059. Jamuna Oil declined to Tk 370 from Tk 414.3 the previous day. Among the other issues on the turnover board, Islami Bank, Grameen Mutual Fund One and IFIC Bank lost. Power Grid Company of Bangladesh and NBL gained. bdn
